\alnum{a} anuguNavAgi; anusAravAgi.

\num{12} \eng{in the line of (duty)} kataRvayx nivaRhaNeyalilx; vaqtitxge saMbaMdhapaTaTx (\kanmu\ jiVvasAvugaLa javAbAdxriyiruva) 
kAyaRdalilx toDagidAga: \eng{a policeman met his death in the line of duty} poliVsinavanu tananx kataRvayx nivaRhaNeyalilx toDagidAdxga 
maraNa hoMdidanu.

tananxdeV (beVTeya) jADu anusarisu; tananxdeV dAriyalilx,
dikikxnalilx, hAdiyalilx, mAgaRdalilx -- hoVgu.  
\num{14} \eng{lay (\engit{or} put) it on the line} 

\alnum{a} (\ashi) haNakoDu; duDuDx piVku; rokakx bicucx.

\alnum{a} aDaDxgoVDeya meVlinaMte; ibabxMdiyAgi; sapxSaTxvAgi idU ilalx adU ilalx eMbaMte.

pUtiR muMdiDu; odagisu. 
\num{16} \eng{out of line with}

\alnum{a} anuguNavAgilalxde; anusAravAgilalxde. 

\alnum{b} oMdeV maTaTxdalilx ilalxde; ErupeVrAgi. 
\hyperdef{L}{line(1) nuga(17)}{}
\num{17} \eng{read between the lines} (dasetxYvaju, BASaNa, \mo vugaLa) gUDhAthaRvanunx kANu, kaMDuhiDi; rahasAyxthaRvanunx patetxhacucx;

certain sadness between the lines} avaLa kAgadaveVnoV sAkaSuTx saMtoVSadiMda
kUDidadxMte kaMDitu, Adare adaroLage
aDagidadx yAvudoV duHKavanunx kaMDe.

\num{19} \eng{translate life etc. into line and colour} bALu
\mo vanunx reVKe matutx baNaNxgaLiMda citirxsu, nirUpisu.}

\noindent
\gl{\akirx}
\dictmeaning{\num{1} (\kanmu\ hoVgalu manasisxlalxde) horaDuvudanunx -- taDamADu, vilaMba mADu; alelxV savxlapx hotutx uLi. 
\num{2} (oMdu sathxLavanunx, viSayavanunx biTuTx muMde hoVgade) alalxlelxV -- tirugADu, sutAtxDu, baLasADu, suLidADu, kAleLe: 
\eng{she lingered in delight over every one of the places} parxtiyoMdu sathxLadalilxyU avaLu adanunx biTuTx muMde hoVgade 
alalxlilxyeV sutAtxDidaLu. \eng{lingered on what they said} avaru heVLidadxnenxV ciMtisutAtx hoVdevu. 
\num{3} alilxyeV uLi; niriVkiSxsida yA sariyAda kAlakekx horaDadiru yA baMdu
seVradiru: \eng{we lingered a while after the party} saMtoVSakUTa mugida meVle
nAvu (horaDuva manasisxlalxde) savxlapx hotutx alilxyeV uLidevu. 
\num{4} (\kanmu\ roVgada \vi) bahukAla eLe; diVGaR kAlaviru: \eng{lingering disease} bahukAla
eLeyuva roVga. \eng{lingering agonies} bahukAla eLeyuva yAtanegaLu. 
\num{5} (roVgadiMda ashakatxrAdavaru, sAyutitxruva roVgi, rUDhiyaLiyutitxruva padadhxtigaLa \vi) usirADikoMDiru; usiru 
hiDidukoMDiru; naraLikoMDiru; naraLutAtx kAlahAku; dubaRlavAgidadxrU uLidukoMDiru; heVgoV kAlayApane mADutitxru, jiVvaviTuTxkoMDiru: 
\eng{he lingered only a few months after his heart attack} haqdayAGAtavAda meVle kelavu tiMgaLugaLu mAtarx avanu 
heVgoV usireLedukoMDidadx. \eng{the custom still lingers (on) in some villages} A padadhxti kelavu haLiLxgaLalilx
inUnx uLidide, jiVvaMtavAgide. 
\num{6} taDamADu; nidhAna, CAnasa, vilaMba -- mADu;
tAmasadiMdiru; yathA sAvakAshavAgiru: \eng{linger in discharging one's duties}
kataRvayxgaLanunx nivaRhisuvudaralilx nidhAnavAgiru, yathA sAvakAshavAgiru.}

-pUtiR; iDi-; velalx: \eng{all day long} hagalelalx; dinavelalx. \eng{life long} bALina udadxkUkx.
